    <h2>Common Issues with Vulcan Commercial Ovens</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Uneven heating or temperature fluctuations</strong> – Often caused by a failing thermostat, heating element, or blocked airflow.</li>
        <li><strong>Gas burner ignition failure</strong> – A faulty igniter, gas valve, or pilot light may prevent proper heating.</li>
        <li><strong>Control panel malfunctions</strong> – Issues with electronic controls or manual dials can affect temperature regulation.</li>
        <li><strong>Excessive grease and carbon buildup</strong> – Can lead to   fire hazards and non-compliance with California health codes  .</li>
        <li><strong>Ventilation and airflow issues</strong> – A blocked exhaust system can cause overheating and inefficient cooking.</li>
        <li><strong>Oven not reaching set temperature</strong> – Due to a faulty thermostat, failing heating elements, or gas supply problems.</li>
        <li><strong>Excessive smoke production</strong> – Often a result of improper airflow, grease accumulation, or malfunctioning burners.</li>
    </ul>
    
